I have a Remington 783 I got for upcoming hunting season. I've shot 60 rounds through it exactly. It retails on buds for $315, but after shipping, taxes, and FFL it runs for closer to $400. The 783 is a new model that came out in 2013. It is not built like the POS 770's, but rather a slight step down from the 700. Everything is solid, fits like a glove. I've owned both and I prefer my 783 over the 700, you just can't modify it that much like a 700. Selling this to pay for college. Going to borrow a buddies rifle for this season. She's lightweight and the synthetic stock will help with scratches when out in the woods. I know a company makes special wood stocks for the 783 for around $80. Sling swivels and one stud installed for the bi pod.

The 783 uses a barrel nut and free float barrel. The bolt is butter, low profile so it doesn't interfere with any scope. Leopold scope already sold so don't ask if I can throw in a optic, don't have one. This is an amazing rifle and was blowing the center out of the targets at 100 yards no problem. Comes with detachable 5 round factory mag.
